<div class=WordSection1>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;line-height:normal'><b><span
style='font-size:24.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Biliary
dyskinesia</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>What is biliary dyskinesia</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Biliary dyskinesia is a
violation of the&nbsp;<b>motility of the&nbsp;</b>biliary tract.&nbsp;Motility
refers to the operation of a system of &quot;valves&quot; and &quot;pumps&quot;
that pump bile from the gallbladder into the duodenum.&nbsp;Motor skills consist
of:&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>the ability of the&nbsp;<b>gallbladder to&nbsp;</b>completely
empty, throwing bile into the ducts;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>the ability of the&nbsp;<b>bile ducts&nbsp;</b>to contract,
pushing bile out;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>the ability of the&nbsp;<b>sphincter of Oddi&nbsp;</b>to open and
close in time, regulating the excretion of bile into the intestinal
lumen.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>The bile system must be
emptied of bile on time and sufficiently.&nbsp;If this does not happen, we can
talk about biliary dyskinesia (&nbsp;<b>BDT&nbsp;</b>).</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>The disease is also known as</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Acalculous cholecystopathy.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>In English, the disease is called:</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:normal'><span
style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Biliary dyskinesia</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Causes</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>DWP is a functional disease,
that is, a disease in which there are no violations in the structure of
internal organs - their work, their coordinated functioning is
disrupted.&nbsp;The reasons for this are not always clear.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Spasm of smooth smooth muscles
of the biliary tract can be caused by psychoemotional (&nbsp;<b>stress,
depression&nbsp;</b>) or hormonal factors.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>The consequences of the&nbsp;<b>operation
to remove the gallbladder&nbsp;</b>may be affected&nbsp;.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>An important role in the
development of dyskinesia is played by the properties of bile itself.&nbsp;When
it is oversaturated with cholesterol and microcrystals, when passing through
the ducts, it can gradually injure their walls, disrupt the work of the
sphincters and provoke chronic inflammation, therefore, the high prevalence of
IDH in the modern world can be partly explained by the epidemic of&nbsp;<b>obesity&nbsp;</b>,
which causes a change in the composition of bile.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Who is at risk</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Obese and sedentary;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>over-consuming food rich in carbohydrates and unhealthy fats;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>those who have previously had their gallbladder removed;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>experiencing depression, neurosis, constant stress.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>How often does it occur</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>The global prevalence of AND
in developed countries is 15-25%.&nbsp;In Russia, according to various sources,
it is from 1% to 15%.&nbsp;It is more often diagnosed in women.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Symptoms</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Pain in the abdomen of varying
intensity: from discomfort to severe&nbsp;<b>biliary&nbsp;</b>(associated with
the biliary system) pain, which is localized in the middle or right upper
abdomen.&nbsp;Pain can radiate to the back, under the right shoulder
blade.&nbsp;They do not depend on food intake, bowel emptying, sometimes
accompanied by nausea and vomiting, which does not bring relief.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Pain can occur for no apparent
reason, sometimes against a background of stress, in the premenstrual period,
after taking medications that have a pronounced effect on the motility of the
biliary tract (estrogens, opioids, somatostatin).</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Diagnosis of the disease</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>As with many other functional
diseases, AVD is diagnosed by exclusion.&nbsp;The doctor must first check for
the presence of all those diseases that cause similar symptoms, but the reasons
for their occurrence are structural changes in the organs (gallbladder stones,
tumors, deformation of the bile ducts, etc.).&nbsp;When it becomes clear that
there are no other lesions, and the characteristic symptoms are present, the
doctor diagnoses DVP.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Biochemical blood test -&nbsp;<b>determination of the level of
transaminases (ALT, AST), pancreatic amylase and lipase, bilirubin&nbsp;</b>.&nbsp;If
the disorder is functional, then the levels of all indicators are either
normal, or slightly increased after painful attacks.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Ultrasound of the&nbsp;</span></b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>abdominal cavity is performed
to exclude cholelithiasis, liver neoplasms, biliary tract, and pancreas.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>EGDS&nbsp;</span></b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>- to exclude peptic ulcer and other
organic lesions of the duodenum.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Ultrasound cholecystography&nbsp;</span></b><span
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>allows
you to assess the contractility of the gallbladder, to understand how
effectively it pushes bile after stimulation.&nbsp;The study is not very
informative, but it can reveal strong deviations.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>If there are suspicions of
other pathologies and complications, then more complex diagnostic methods may
be prescribed: magnetic resonance cholangiopancreatography, endoscopic
ultrasound of the pancreatobiliary zone, endoscopic retrograde
cholangiopancreatography and sphincter of Oddi manometry.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Treatment</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Lifestyle and aids</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Diet is very important for
AVP.&nbsp;Frequent and fractional meals are recommended, limit animal fats,
fried foods, strong meat and fish broths, canned food and smoked meats, spices,
seasonings and spices, marinades, carbonated drinks, beer, coffee, citrus
fruits, fermented milk products, cereals, bananas, baked apples are useful ,
mashed potatoes, vegetable soups, boiled meat (lean beef, chicken breast), some
mineral waters.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>It is better to cook food, stew,
bake, steam.&nbsp;For 1.5-2 hours after eating, long bends and horizontal
position should be avoided.&nbsp;Outside the period of exacerbation, the diet
is expanded and, with good tolerance, food is organized according to the usual
principles.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Considering the influence of
the psychoemotional state on the motility of the biliary tract, the patient
needs to normalize sleep, daily regimen, and provide himself with good rest.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Medications</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Antispasmodics such as&nbsp;<b>hyoscine butyl bromide, mebeverine,
trimebutin, and gimecromone&nbsp;</b>.&nbsp;The latter acts selectively on the
sphincter of Oddi.&nbsp;The most common antispasmodic -&nbsp;<b>drotaverine&nbsp;</b>(no-shpa)
can also be used, but it does not have a high selectivity of action on the
biliary tract.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Ursodeoxycholic acid&nbsp;</span></b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>improves the quality of bile
and has an anti-inflammatory effect on the epithelium and muscle layer of the
biliary tract.&nbsp;Do not take with pancreatitis.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Prokinetics (&nbsp;<b>itopride&nbsp;</b>,&nbsp;<b>domperidone&nbsp;</b>)
are used to eliminate discomfort: nausea, bloating, heaviness in the
abdomen.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs&nbsp;</span></b><span
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>can be
used once, to relieve pain.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>If there is good reason to suspect a neurogenic cause of
pain,&nbsp;<b>antidepressants&nbsp;</b>such as amitriptyline&nbsp;may be
used&nbsp;.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Surgical operations</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>These are endoscopic&nbsp;<b>papillosphincterotomy&nbsp;</b>for
dysfunction of the sphincter of Oddi and&nbsp;<b>cholecystectomy&nbsp;</b>for
gallbladder dyskinesia.&nbsp;With DVT, they are rarely performed, for very
compelling medical reasons and in the absence of drug
effect.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Possible complications</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Since VAD may be associated
with bile quality, there is a predisposition to&nbsp;</span><b><u><span
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:blue'><a
href="file:///F:\pechen-i-zhelchevyvodyashchiye-puti%20(GUTARDY)\diskineziya-zhelchevyvodyashchikh-putei.html"
target="_blank">gallstones</a></span></u></b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<b>biliary
pancreatitis&nbsp;</b>.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Prophylaxis</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Healthy lifestyle;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>maintaining optimal weight;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>physical activity.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Forecast</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>The general prognosis for the
course of the veins is usually favorable.&nbsp;However, dysfunction of the
sphincter of Oddi can cause excruciating symptoms and contribute to a decrease
in working capacity, and be the reason for frequent seeking medical help.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
